page.title: 06Surprise at Panshangar.
page.content: We were at school looking at a map of Panshangar.The map was mostly trees and fields and on the other side of the road was a school. There was also a small airfield.We went there and saw lots of houses. There were small woods and a airfield behind the houses but we saw the school so it must be the right place .We were really confused because we expected trees and fields. It was a surprise we trusted the map to be right but the map was wrong,so you can,t trust a map all the time.The last time it was changed was in 1981 so the houses were built in the last 4 years so when the next update comes they will have alot of work to do.The builders had not finished making the houses because they were still making the houses because they were still working on the houses.The builders yards were still there.
